Program for calculating Simple Interest

* Where a Loan is taken out with an annual interest rate of 9%. 

* Monthly payments of 165,25â‚¬ each. 

* Program keeps track or remaining balance owed 

Formula for balance is balk = ( PMT. (1 - (1+i)^(k-n)))/ i 

balk =  balance remaining after the kth payment
k    = payment number 
PMT  = amount of monthly payment
i    = interest rate per month 
n    = total number of payments to be made
